    en: "Catalytic converter theft is a persistent problem in New York. Thieves can cut a converter off a parked car in a few minutes. The 2022 catalytic converter law (Chapter 619 of the Laws of 2022) treats the catalytic converter as a major component part under Vehicle and Traffic Law 415-a and tightens scrap metal dealer rules under General Business Law Article 6-C. A theft victim should file a police report, which is the trigger for most auto insurance claims. Comprehensive auto insurance covers replacement minus the deductible; liability-only coverage does not."
